---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { referenceTracks } from "@/lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="Reference" description="The current reference map for Kern language, runtime, compiler, and package behavior.">
  <section class="manual-page mx-auto px-5 pb-20 pt-14 md:px-8 md:pt-18">
    <div class="eyebrow">Reference</div>
    <h1 class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-5xl leading-[0.95] text-[color:var(--kern-ink)] md:text-6xl">
      Reference
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[color:rgba(21,26,32,0.76)]">
      This page maps the current reference surface on the website. Some parts are
      already website-native; others still point at authoritative repository documents.
    </p>

    <div class="manual-callout mt-10">
      <div class="manual-kicker">Reference Summary</div>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-base">
        <li>Language, runtime, compiler driver, and package manager each have separate reference tracks.</li>
        <li>Website-native pages should only replace repository docs when they are equally authoritative.</li>
        <li>Until then, this index should point to the real source of truth instead of hiding the transition.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section class="manual-section">
      <h2>Reference tracks</h2>
      <div class="manual-directory mt-6">
        {
          referenceTracks.map((track) => (
            <div class="manual-directory-item">
              <div class="manual-directory-heading">
                <div class="manual-directory-title">{track.title}</div>
                <div class="manual-directory-meta">Reference</div>
              </div>
              <div class="manual-directory-body">{track.description}</div>
              <div class="manual-directory-links">
                <a href={track.href}>Open website reference</a>
                <a href={track.sourceHref} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open repository source</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="manual-section">
      <h2>Migration rule</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base">
        Website-native reference pages should replace repository docs only when
        they become equally authoritative and are maintained with the same discipline.
        Until then, this index should continue to point at the current source of truth.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
